com.esri.mo2.data.gcd
Interface PropertySequence

All Known Implementing Classes:
BasePropertySequence
public interface PropertySequence

Defines an ordered collection of properties where each property is a pair of a name and an associated value. There can be more than one value per name, and each value can be a collection of elements. There can also be several (more than one) identical properties in a PropertySequence.

Invariant:
the number of all property names is equal to the number of all property values, i.e.
this.getNames().length == this.getValues().length

overrideProperties

public void overrideProperties(PropertySequence ops)
overrides properties of this property sequence with the ones of the incomming ops. If a property of ops is not present in this property sequence, it is appended there. If a property of ops is present in this property sequence several times than the first occurrence is overriden.

Parameters:
ops - PropertySequence whose elements are used to override this PropertySequence
Precondition:
ops != null
Postcondition:
each property of ops is present in this PropertySequence. Also, for each property of ops, if the original PropertySequence contained at least one property with the same name as the property of ops, then the first such property is overridden with the property of ops. For example, if original property sequence is {(a,3), (b,7), (a,4)} and ops is {(a,100), (a,200), (a,200)}, the resulting this property sequence is {(a,100), (b,7), (a,200), (a,200)}

overrideProperty

public void overrideProperty(int ind,
                             String name,
                             Object value)
overrides the property at the given index of this PropertySequence with the given name and value. If the given index is out of bounds, this PropertySequence is left unchanged.

Parameters:
ind - index of the property to be overridden
name - new name of the property at index ind
value - new value of the property at index ind
Precondition:
TRUE
Postcondition:
if index ind is within bounds, this PropertySequence contains a property with name name and value value at index ind and the property that used to be in the original PropertySequence at index ind is removed. If index ind is out of bounds, this PropertySequence is the same as the original PropertySequence, i.e.
((0 <= ind < original.getCount()) ==>
(this.getName(ind) <==> name) && (this.getValue(ind) <==> value)) &&
((ind < 0 || ind >= original.getCount()) ==> (original <==> this))
